OL,6,FMs Prakash said the victim, who had
OL,7,Flimited speech, was not able to say
OL,8,Fwhat happened but kept apologising.
OL,10,FLater that night, Ms Prakash heard
OL,11,Fcrying from the victim's room and
OL,12,Ffound Vieria with her - which is
OL,13,Fagainst proper practice as at least
OL,14,Ftwo nurses should deal with a resident.
OL,16,FMs Prakash added that the victim was
OL,17,Fvisibly upset and hiding her face.
OL,19,FMs Prakash again asked Vieria and Ms
OL,20,FManuel what had happened, but said
OL,21,Fthey both denied knowing anything.
